  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> as thinly as you can into rounds (save the rest for later!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681486947077-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681486947077-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681486947077-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681486947077-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681486947077-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>lemon rounds</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over so that they start to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> lemon rounds</strong> to a small bowl with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cover with<strong> boiled water </strong>then set aside until later – this is your<strong> speedy preserved lemon</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681486950363-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681486950363-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681486950363-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681486950363-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681486950363-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over medium-high heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>thighs</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season them generously on both sides with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> ras el hanout</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>thighs</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 10 min or until the skins have browned and crisped</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681486954839-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681486954839-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681486954839-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681486954839-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681486954839-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>to a baking tray with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ras el hanout</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 12 min or until cooked through and charred</p><p>After an initial 12 min, add your <strong>flaked almonds </strong>to the opposite side of the tray and return the tray to the oven for a further 3-4 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681486962009-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
